We can use a stack to keep track of chars. We will iterate through the string and if a char is a '(' 
we will push it to the stack, else if it is a ')' we will check to see if this closes any open parentheses 
in the stack. If it does, we will pop an element of the stack and record the length of the current 
valid substring. Then, we will iterate through the stack to get the the longest valid substring.

class Solution {
    public int longestValidParentheses(String s) {
        Stack<Integer> stack = new Stack<>();
        int maxLen = 0;
        stack.push(-1);
        for (int i = 0; i < s.length(); i++) {
            char ch = s.charAt(i);
            if (ch == '(') stack.push(i);
            else {
                stack.pop();
                if (!stack.isEmpty()) {
                    maxLen = Math.max(maxLen, i - stack.peek());
                }
                else {
                    stack.push(i);
                }
            }
        }
        return maxLen;
    }
}

